External knowledge:
- Client hierarchy is established based on the client-agent assignment, where top-level clients do not have an assigned agent;
- The query assumes that the client-agent relationship is hierarchical, i.e., a client can be assigned to another client who acts as an agent;
- The query does not filter by specific client types or statuses, implying it aims to provide a comprehensive list of all clients in the system.
